Camtek Ltd. (CAMT)  slid the most in more
than four months after the maker of optical-inspection systems
reported a fourth-quarter loss yesterday.  The  shares  tumbled 8.3 percent, the most since Oct. 4, to
8.705 shekels, or the equivalent of $2.33, at 12:37 p.m. in  Tel
Aviv , bringing the two-day drop to 11 percent. The companyâ€™s
U.S. traded shares plunged 11 percent to $2.4 yesterday.  Camtek reported a net loss of $1.9 million after a profit
of $1.3 million in the year-earlier period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
